SpcPopNotes: Pande et al. (2007) conducted an ornithological expedition to the Lakshadweep archipelago in March 2006. They reported 5,000 Sooty Terns (with 48% pairs breeding), 1,700 Brown Noddies, 1,900 Large Crested Terns, 760 Lesser Crested Terns and 40 White-cheeked Terns on Cherbaniani Island and found 1,200 eggs.
